</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR205:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR205"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              205-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 205</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 138</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Congenital Cytomegalovirus Awareness Month. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 26, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 205, Lackey.
                          Congenital Cytomegalovirus Awareness Month.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would declare the month of June 2026 as Congenital Cytomegalovirus Awareness Month.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_AEF5F523-C73E-4DCE-BEDF-D1CD4B640F0D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Congenital cytomegalovirus (cCMV) is a common virus that infects people of all ages and is the most common infectious cause of birth defects in the United States, affecting approximately 1 in 200 infants; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_9227170A-F7A0-42A1-9BCE-32011D258B5F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Approximately 1 in 5 children born with cCMV will experience permanent health problems, including hearing loss, vision impairment, developmental and motor delays, and other serious medical conditions; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B43CC486-8AB8-4DAC-855A-48248E2502E0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, cCMV is a leading nongenetic cause of childhood hearing loss; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_739D729C-B621-4F04-907B-A95E0A81718D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Despite its prevalence and potential severity, awareness of cCMV among pregnant individuals and the general public remains low; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6BF3EA11-624A-4469-B1D9-15885E76C401"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Increased public awareness and education about cCMV, including preventative hygiene practices during pregnancy, have the potential to reduce transmission and improve maternal and child health outcomes; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_454FAB63-B1A3-49CC-8B34-3010570282A1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Early detection and timely intervention can significantly improve outcomes for infants born with cCMV; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D16F6499-D4CA-4CAC-98B9-E9A0C03604D4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Families affected by cCMV often face complex medical, emotional, and caregiving challenges and benefit from increased awareness, support, and access to resources; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_700A01C3-A29B-488C-BE28-030A55BB37D0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Advocacy organizations, including the National CMV Foundation, along with dedicated California-based advocates and community leaders, are working to increase awareness, support affected families, and advance research efforts related to cCMV; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_699E3405-40B2-414D-8274-D5B818F6663C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The State of California recognizes the importance of collaborative efforts among health care providers, advocacy organizations, and community leaders to improve awareness, prevention, and outcomes related to cCMV; now, therefore, be it </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_4A14345E-7E83-4C70-BED8-37D03E8836E6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature recognizes the month of June 2026 as Congenital Cytomegalovirus Awareness Month in the State of California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_78C8A2ED-D056-4744-BF2F-3D717F2B3D44"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature honors the ongoing efforts of national and California-based organizations, advocates, and families working to raise awareness of cCMV and support those impacted by this condition; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_9A87BD3A-4162-4576-BA0D-CC124862A827"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That all Californians are encouraged to become informed about cCMV, including methods of prevention, transmission risks, and the importance of early detection; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_1B24AD62-2023-483D-BA3C-0207D169DD98"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That health care providers, public health agencies, and community organizations are encouraged to promote education and awareness of cCMV to improve maternal and child health outcomes across California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_B54E8A2B-D50D-4B30-AAF1-B753DFB5012F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to appropriate state and local health agencies, interested organizations, and the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
